Sentencas: In this paper, a GdBaCo2O5+delta-Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 (GBCO-SDC) composite cathode was prepared by the impregnation method with GdBaCo2O5+delta (GBCO) as the impregnating phase and Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 (SDC) as the cathode skeleton.
Titulo: Comparison of the oxygen reduction mechanisms in a GBCO-SDC-impregnated cathode and a GBCO cathode

Sentencas: X-ray diffraction (XRD) analysis showed a good chemical compatibility between GBCO and SDC, and there were no obvious impurities at high temperature.
Titulo: Comparison of the oxygen reduction mechanisms in a GBCO-SDC-impregnated cathode and a GBCO cathode

Sentencas: The particle size of GBCO was approximately 80 nm.
Titulo: Comparison of the oxygen reduction mechanisms in a GBCO-SDC-impregnated cathode and a GBCO cathode

Sentencas: The continuous GBCO phase was deposited on the surface of porous SDC backbones, which greatly improved the electrochemical activity of the cathode.
Titulo: Comparison of the oxygen reduction mechanisms in a GBCO-SDC-impregnated cathode and a GBCO cathode

Sentencas: The polarization resistance of GBCO-SDC-impregnated cathode was 0.50 omega cm(2) at 600 degrees C, which was only 28.6% of that of pure GBCO cathode.
Titulo: Comparison of the oxygen reduction mechanisms in a GBCO-SDC-impregnated cathode and a GBCO cathode

Sentencas: The oxygen reduction reaction (ORR) at GBCO cathode mainly involved the adsorption-dissociation of oxygen molecules and charge-transfer process of oxygen atoms.
Titulo: Comparison of the oxygen reduction mechanisms in a GBCO-SDC-impregnated cathode and a GBCO cathode

Sentencas: The two ORR rate-controlling steps were the adsorption-dissociation process at 500-600 degrees C and the charge-transfer processes at 600-700 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Comparison of the oxygen reduction mechanisms in a GBCO-SDC-impregnated cathode and a GBCO cathode

Sentencas: The oxygen reduction reaction at GBCO-SDC-impregnated cathode mainly involved the diffusion of oxygen ions through the three phase boundaries and the charge transfer of oxygen atoms, in which the charge-transfer process was always the ORR rate-controlling step.
Titulo: Comparison of the oxygen reduction mechanisms in a GBCO-SDC-impregnated cathode and a GBCO cathode
